description.narrative: The health system has improved capacity to provide a package of high-impact health interventions equitably for mothers, children and adolescents., which contributes to Child Health, Child Health (Covid), Hiv Prevention, Immunization, Immunization (Covid), Maternal And Newborn Health, Maternal And Newborn Health (Covid), Treatment And Care Of Children Living With Hiv. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: 1. By 2022, newborns, children under-five, adolescents, and pregnant and lactating women, increasingly utilize quality health, nutrition HIV and WASH services and families adopt healthy and hygienic behaviours and practices, including during emergencies.
